The All Progressives Congress (APC) is et to put to an end speculations about zoning of party offices in the build up to the party’s national convention in March and general elections in 2023.
The National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC), Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe State on Wednesday disclosed the appointment of the APC Zoning Committee for the March National Convention head by Governor AbdulRahaman AbdulRazak of Kwara State.
The APC Zoning Committee comprises of Governor AbdulRahaman AbdulRazak of Kwara State, Chairman; the Deputy President of the Senate, Ovie Omo-Agege, Deputy Chairman; Prof.  Etim Nyong – Member, Dr. MB Shehu – Member, Comrade Mustapha Salihu – Member, Sen. Teslim Folarin – Member, Alh. Sadeeq Sule-Iko Sami – Member, Deputy Governor Nkem Okeke of Anambra State, Secretary.
The Committee is expected to submit its report on Monday 7th March 2022.
